GV’s Got Talent is back & this year it is bigger and better!🎤💃⚓️⬆️

Join us on Wednesday, March 15 at 7 p.m. in the Grand River Room, KC 2250 for one of the biggest talent shows on campus! Interested in performing? See information below.

AUDITION INFORMATION:

Dates:
🔹Sunday, February 26 from 10 a.m. – 5 p.m.
🔹Monday, February 27 from 12 – 3 p.m.
 
Provided Equipment:
🔹Two microphones, laptop, surround sound, and an XLR cable
 
Rules and Regulations:
🔹Performances can be any category – singing, dancing, poetry, magic, comedy, DJing, etc.
🔹Performances cannot exceed 5 minutes
🔹Performances cannot contain hate speech, racial slurs, or derogatory language
🔹The stage dimensions are 24x16 feet
🔹Group performances are welcome but note that prize amount is per act, not per person
 
Prizes:
🔹First-place: Perform as the opener for the Spring Concert headliner (April 1) & earn a $200 academic scholarship
🔹Second-place: Earn a $100 academic scholarship
🔹Third-place: Earn a $50 academic scholarship
**Please note, prizes are per act, not per person**

Signups:
🔹Link in bio

Everyone who auditions will be notified by Friday, March 3 whether or not they were chosen to perform at GV's Got Talent on March 15.

Stephen Agyei is a Stand-Up Comedian, Actor and writer who hails from Denver, CO. Noted for having the whitest teeth in Denver, he became one of the city’s most sought-after comedians. Shining brightly with his mischievous smile, the Comedy Works regular was the winner of the 2012 Comedy Works’ Clean Comedy Contest, and 3-time finalist in the venue’s New Faces contest; With a style described as “calculated fearlessness.”

The LA-based comedian has been featured on Just For Laughs Digital, Viceland’s Flophouse and NPR’s “All Things Considered” with Roy Wood Jr. You may also have seen him in his commercial work for Realtor.com, Remi Martin(Directed by Jake Nava), and Voiceover on BoJack Horseman, on Netflix. He will also be featured on the upcoming season of Cartoon Network’s Tig-N-Seek.

Do you want to pursue a Master’s degree in Higher Education and plan university-wide events? Apply to GVSU’s Master of Education in Higher Education (CSAL) program. Once admitted into the program, all admitted students have the opportunity to apply for the Programming Graduate Assistant in the Office of Student Life position. This position helps coordinate and implement student life programs and events, and co-advises the Campus Activities Board. Benefits include tuition waiver and stipend. Apply at gvsu.edu/csal ⬆️⚓️

Have questions about the program or position? Reach out the second-year Programming Graduate Assistant, Chad Novak, at s_novakcha@gvsu.edu or reach out to the program @gvsu_highereducation/@gvsusaga!

Juneteenth is the oldest nationally celebrated commemoration of the ending of slavery in the United States.
From its Galveston, Texas origin in 1865, the observance of June 19th as the African American Emancipation Day has spread across the United States and beyond.

For more info please visit juneteenth.com
